-- France Halts New Solar Power Projects Before Price Talks, Les Echos Says
-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 2010-12-03T05:58:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-03/france-halts-new-solar-power-projects-before-price-talks-les-echos-says.html
The French government has put all new
solar power projects, except those under 3 kilowatts undertaken
by individuals, on hold, pending talks on a new pricing
structure, Les Echos reported.  The move is designed to stop a glut of project requests
ahead of a possible cut in government solar power purchasing
tariffs, the daily newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  